# agents-control-tower -- Project Context

## What this is
Retro terminal TUI for launching, monitoring, and commanding Cursor AI agents (cloud + local). Built with Ink 5 (React for terminals) + TypeScript.

## Architecture
```
src/
  index.tsx          Entry point, renders <App />
  app.tsx            Root component, screen router, keyboard nav
  components/        TUI components (header, tables, detail, launch, etc.)
  hooks/             React hooks (useCloudAgents, useConfig, useRepos, useModels, useElapsed)
  lib/
    cursor-api.ts    Cursor Cloud Agents REST API client
    config.ts        Config persistence (~/.agents-control-tower/config.json)
    types.ts         All TypeScript types
```

## Cursor Cloud API shape (critical)
- Statuses are UPPERCASE: RUNNING, FINISHED, ERROR, CREATING, EXPIRED
- Agent has nested `source` (repository, ref) and `target` (branchName, url, prUrl)
- Agent name is in `agent.name`, not in prompt
- Conversation messages use `type` (user_message/assistant_message) and `text`
- Models endpoint returns string[] not objects
- Repos endpoint is /v0/repositories (returns owner, name, repository)
- Follow-up endpoint is /v0/agents/{id}/followup (not /follow-up)
- Key validation uses /v0/me
- API key link: cursor.com/dashboard?tab=integrations

## Key constraints
- Ink Box does NOT have backgroundColor prop in v5
- Raw mode required (won't run in non-TTY shells like IDE terminals)
- npm package name: agents-control-tower
- Published under ofershap npm account

## Build/test
- `npm run dev` -- tsx src/index.tsx
- `npm run build` -- tsup (ESM, node20 target)
- `npm test` -- vitest
- `npm run typecheck` -- tsc --noEmit
